(128, 'GET_ACCOUNTS', 'android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS', NULL, 'Allows access to the list of accounts in the Accounts Service.', 'Beginning with Android 6.0 (API level 23), if an app shares the signature of the authenticator that manages an account, it does not need \"GET_ACCOUNTS\" permission to read information about that account. On Android 5.1 and lower, all apps need \"GET_ACCOUNTS\" permission to read information about any account.', 'dangerous', 1, 0, NULL, 0, 12, NULL, 'Android', 'Find accounts on the device', 'Allows the app to get the list of accounts known by the phone. This may include any accounts created by applications you have installed.', 'Dangerous', '2024-02-05 03:53:29'),
